The paper deals with multi-agent systems and learning, which falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The use of communication networks and graphs suggests that the paper may also fall under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The mean-field approximation method used in the paper is a common technique in machine learning, which suggests that the paper may also fall under Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the interplay between randomness and social interaction, which suggests that it may fall under Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of bounded local memory suggests that the paper may also fall under Information Theory (cs.IT).
